# 19. 10-Second Interview Answer

"Merge Sort is a stable Divide and Conquer sorting algorithm. It recursively divides the array into halves until single elements remain, then merges the sorted halves using two pointers. It guarantees O(n log n) time complexity in all cases but requires O(n) extra space. It is widely used in linked list sorting, inversion counting, and external sorting systems."
